While DECODE is concise, most modern SQL developers (and other databases like PostgreSQL or SQL Server) prefer
the CASE statement because it is easier to read and part of the SQL standard:

SELECT DECODE( address,'302668', add1,'78564', add2, '785456', add3) as st_cd
FROM CUSTOMERS ;



SELECT 
    CASE address
        WHEN '302668' THEN add1
        WHEN '78564'  THEN add2
        WHEN '785456' THEN add3
        ELSE NULL -- Optional
    END AS st_cd
FROM CUSTOMERS;
